.TH "bee-remove" "1" "2012-08-31" "bee @BEE_VERSION@" "bee - bau et einfach"

.SH "NAME"
bee\-remove \- Remove an installed bee package

.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.SY "bee remove"
.OP options
.I <bee-package>
.YS

.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.P
Use
.B bee-remove
to remove installed bee packages. If
.I <bee-package>
does not match the full name of a bee package, all matching packages will be displayed.

.SH "OPTIONS"
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print a little help screen.

.TP
.B \-v, \-\-verbose
Print removed files and directories.

.SH "ENVIRONMENT"
.TP
.B BEE_METADIR
.RS
Directory searched for installed bee packages

